 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-d4b","title":"P1.3 Add provenance columns to conversations table","description":"# Add Provenance Columns to conversations Table

## Context
Each conversation needs to know where it came from. This is the critical change that enables multi-source support and fixes identity collisions.

## Location
src/storage/sqlite.rs

## Schema Changes

### New Columns
\`\`\`sql
ALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN source_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'local' REFERENCES sources(id);
ALTER TABLE conversations ADD COLUMN origin_host TEXT;
\`\`\`

### Updated Uniqueness (CRITICAL)
Current: UNIQUE(agent_id, external_id)
New: UNIQUE(source_id, agent_id, external_id)

This prevents identity collisions when the same agent produces the same external_id on different machines.

## Migration Complexity
SQLite cannot ALTER UNIQUE constraints in place. Migration requires:

1. Create new table with correct schema
2. Copy data from old table (all existing conversations get source_id='local')
3. Drop old table
4. Rename new table
5. Recreate indexes and foreign keys

### Migration SQL
\`\`\`sql
-- Create new table
CREATE TABLE conversations_new (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
    agent_id INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES agents(id),
    workspace_id INTEGER REFERENCES workspaces(id),
    source_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'local' REFERENCES sources(id),
    external_id TEXT,
    title TEXT,
    source_path TEXT NOT NULL,
    started_at INTEGER,
    ended_at INTEGER,
    approx_tokens INTEGER,
    metadata_json TEXT,
    origin_host TEXT,
    UNIQUE(source_id, agent_id, external_id)
);

-- Copy data
INSERT INTO conversations_new 
SELECT id, agent_id, workspace_id, 'local', external_id, title, source_path,
       started_at, ended_at, approx_tokens, metadata_json, NULL
FROM conversations;

-- Swap tables
DROP TABLE conversations;
ALTER TABLE conversations_new RENAME TO conversations;

-- Recreate indexes
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_conv_agent_started ON conversations(agent_id, started_at);
\`\`\`

## Alternative: Backup & Rebuild Strategy
Given that conversations is a rebuildable cache (we can always rescan agent logs), consider:
1. Detect incompatible schema
2. Backup old DB to agent_search.db.bak-{timestamp}
3. Create fresh DB with new schema
4. Trigger full reindex on next run

This is simpler and safer for users, though slower (requires full rescan).

## Recommendation
Implement BOTH:
- Try table-rewrite migration first
- If migration fails, fall back to backup+rebuild
- Log clearly what happened

## API Updates
Update persist_conversation() to accept source_id and origin_host parameters.

## Dependencies
- P1.2 (sources table must exist for FK)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] source_id column added (defaults to 'local')
- [ ] origin_host column added
- [ ] Uniqueness constraint updated
- [ ] Migration tested with existing data
- [ ] Backup+rebuild fallback works
- [ ] persist_conversation updated
- [ ] Tests verify no collisions across sources","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"","created_at":"2025-12-16T05:54:53.788672Z","updated_at":"2025-12-16T07:07:59.248659Z","closed_at":"2025-12-16T07:07:59.248659Z","close_reason":"Added source_id and origin_host columns to conversations table. Updated unique constraint to (source_id, agent_id, external_id). MIGRATION_V5 handles table rewrite for SQLite. All CRUD operations updated to use provenance columns. All tests pass.","compaction_level":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-d4b","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-115","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-12-16T05:56:13.829013Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
